nown for his heartfelt advocacy for Tibetans worldwide and his lifelong interest in modern science.<\/p><p>The 14th Dalai Lama was born in <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Amdo\" title=\"Amdo\">Amdo<\/a>, <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Tibet\" title=\"Tibet\">Tibet<\/a>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Tenzin_Gyatso#cite_note-4\"><span>[<\/span>4<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> and was selected as the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Tulku\" title=\"Tulku\">tulku<\/a> of the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/13th_Dalai_Lama\" title=\"13th Dalai Lama\">13th Dalai Lama<\/a> in 1937 and formally recognized as the 14th Dalai Lama at a public declaration near the town of Bumchen in 1939.<sup id=\"cite_ref-dlce_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Tenzin_Gyatso#cite_note-dlce-5\"><span>[<\/span>5<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> His enthronement ceremony as the Dalai Lama was held in Lhasa on February 22, 1940 and he eventually assumed full temporal (political) power over Tibet on 17 November 1950, at the age of 15, after <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/History_of_Tibet_(1950%E2%80%93present)\" title=\"History of Tibet (1950\u2013present)\">China's invasion of Tibet<\/a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-dlce_5-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Tenzin_Gyatso#cite_note-dlce-5\"><span>[<\/span>5<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> The Dalai Lama's government administered an area roughly corresponding to the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Tibet_Autonomous_Region\" title=\"Tibet Autonomous Region\">Tibet Autonomous Region<\/a> just as the nascent <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/China\" title=\"China\">People's Republic of China<\/a> wished to assert central control over it.<\/p><p>During the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/1959_Tibetan_uprising\" title=\"1959 Tibetan uprising\">1959 Tibetan uprising<\/a>, the Dalai Lama fled to <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/India\" title=\"India\">India<\/a>, where he denounced the Chinese Communist Party and established the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Nongovernmental_organization\" title=\"Nongovernmental organization\" class=\"mw-redirect\">nongovernmental<\/a> <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Central_Tibetan_Administration\" title=\"Central Tibetan Administration\">Central Tibetan Administration<\/a>. He has since traveled the world, advocating for the welfare of Tibetans, teaching Tibetan Buddhism, investigating the interface between <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Buddhism_and_science\" title=\"Buddhism and science\">Buddhism and science<\/a> and talking about the importance of compassion as the source of a happy life. Around the world, institutions face pressure from China not to accept him.<\/p><p>The policy of the Dalai Lama until he retired from politics in 2011<sup id=\"cite_ref-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Tenzin_Gyatso#cite_note-6\"><span>[<\/span>6<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> was that he did not seek sovereignty for Tibet, but would accept Tibet as a genuine autonomous region within the People's Republic of China.<sup id=\"cite_ref-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Tenzin_Gyatso#cite_note-7\"><span>[<\/span>7<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> He has spoken about the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Environmental_quality\" title=\"Environmental quality\">environment<\/a>, <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Economics\" title=\"Economics\">economics<\/a>, <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Women%27s_rights\" title=\"Women's rights\">women's rights<\/a>, <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Non-violence\" title=\"Non-violence\" class=\"mw-redirect\">non-violence<\/a>, <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Interfaith_dialogue\" title=\"Interfaith dialogue\">interfaith dialogue<\/a>, <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Physics\" title=\"Physics\">physics<\/a>, <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Astronomy\" title=\"Astronomy\">astronomy<\/a>, <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Buddhism_and_science\" title=\"Buddhism and science\">Buddhism and science<\/a>, <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Cognitive_neuroscience\" title=\"Cognitive neuroscience\">cognitive neuroscience<\/a>, <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Reproductive_health\" title=\"Reproductive health\">reproductive health<\/a>, and <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Human_sexuality\" title=\"Human sexuality\">sexuality<\/a>, along with various <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Mahayana\" title=\"Mahayana\">Mahayana<\/a> and <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Vajrayana\" title=\"Vajrayana\">Vajrayana<\/a> topics.<\/p>","name":"Tenzin Gyatso","place_of_birth":"Taktser ,  Qinghai ,  Tibet","place_of_death":null,"text":"Tenzin Gyatso , Peace, 1989","year":1989.0}